docs.lead_paragraph: The testimony in the Walton-Matthews murder case was quite interesting yesterday. The evidence for the prosecution closed, and that of the defence was also nearly all in at the adjournment of the Court. Mr. HOLMES opened for the defence. The principal witness was Mrs. WALTON, mother of the prisoner. Several witnesses were examined, with a view to break down the testimony of Officer MOORE.
